{{DISPLAYTITLE:...}}<span class="page-title">A Familiar Darkness</span>

Light is especially appreciated after darkness.

<span class="wds-button mw-customtoggle-sidebar1"><</span>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-sidebar1">
<div class="sidebar-container">
<div class="sidebar-content">
<div class="story-box">
When we got separated while running from the ERC terrorists, I dashed into a hallway that, in the rush of adrenaline, I didn’t even notice how far it went. That ended up being a huge mistake. After taking a breather, I realized I was on a completely different level. I tried using my wall-walking trick to go back and go to our meeting point, but instead of returning where I wanted, I ended up here. This strange place… it’s so dark, so suffocating.
The alleys are so narrow it’s hard to squeeze through, and the silence is unbearable. But when that silence breaks (even slightly) my heart feels like it’s going to stop right then and there. There are these larvae, glowing with a faint blue light, crawling around the corners; they were serving as my only guide, even if their light was so dim. We’ve been through a lot of strange, awful places before, but this one… this one feels stranger. Worse. And I don’t even know why.
The houses line the streets as if people still live there. (I think I’ve seen them before? Do I know this place?) Inside, there’s furniture, electricity, even running water. Everything looks “normal,” but I don’t trust it. I don’t feel safe. It’s like I’m being watched, like guilt itself is pressing down on my shoulders, as if I’m being judged for some mistake I can’t even remember.
I kept walking and tried to grab my flashlight, but nearly fainted when I realized it was gone from my pack. In its place was a camera. My batteries did work on them, but every time I took a picture, a blinding flash lasted only a few seconds before everything was back into darkness. That’s when I realized finding you again wouldn't be easy.
<div style="margin-top: -30px">[[File:237_Camera.png|center|300px]]</div>
</div></div></div><div class="light-overlay"></div></div>'''''Item-#:'''''
<div style="font-size: 32px">'''Level 301'''</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 9px">Level properly categorized and identified.</div>
{{Class Custom Image|class=Undetermined|text-color=#FFFFFF|safety=Unknown Safety|security=Unguaranteed Security|entity=Low Entity Count|hexagon=?|bg-image=Dark_Labyrinth_Header.png|bg-size=760px|color-h=45|color-s=45|color-l=45}}

<div style="text-align: justify;">
Level 301 is the 302th level of the Backrooms. For its dark enviroment and its cognitohazard properties, its known as "Personal Purgatory", or "Familiar Darkness".
</div>

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level_191.png|hovertext=Why are they judging us?|caption=Picture taken by a Wanderer on '''Level 301'''}}
<div style="text-align: justify;">
The level looks like a late-night 1990's suburban area with rundown houses and tight alleys that curve at geometrically impossible angles (overlapping prior alleys would be physically there), with passageways hard even for one person to squeeze through. The atmosphere is a mix of familiarity and strangeness, like it was forcing itself to feel nostalgic. The level is not entirely stable, for its landscape is formed in a limited way, as if it were low-rendered; only the nearby blocks are visible, while the rest is hidden by a gray fog. A persistent wind sweeps through the streets, rattling loose shutters and whispering, yet the fog remains completely still, unaffected by the breeze. The level keeps the wanderer away from encountering any human being; for that, its called "Personal Purgatory."
{{Audio|file=Level_191_Ambience.mp3|volume=0.2}}
The level is extremely dark, with only the faint purple-blueish light of Glowing Larvaes, present on the whole level, guiding the wanderer on the sidewalks, alleys and sometimes leading into houses. If the wanderer enters the level with even the faintest light source, from matches to flashlights, it gets replaced by a polaroid camera with a flash so bright it can momentarily illuminate a considerable amount of area.

The interior of the houses is accessible, yet to enter them is not advisable. Every house appears to mirror parts of the wanderer's own memories, yet never accurately. Rooms are known appear to be distorted; childhood bedrooms with furnitures on the ceiling, empty kitchens in which the clock is ticking backwards, living rooms in which the furniture cycles itself in a never-ending loop. The houses wallpaper occasionally beats like they are living, and windows display different streets than what is seen outdoors.

<span class="wds-button mw-customtoggle-sidebar2"><</span>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-sidebar2">
<div class="sidebar-container"><div class="sidebar-content">
<div class="story-box">
I’m seeing things. While trying to fit through one of the alleyways, I heard something, no, I saw something! It was our mother’s face, I’m sure of it! She was screaming for help from a window of one of the houses. I tried to run through the alley as fast as I could, and my nose started bleeding. When I blinked, the window was gone, and I wasn’t even inside an alley.
[[File:237_Window.png|300px|center]]
I’ve been here for a long time already, and so far I haven’t seen a single sign of life besides the larvae, but I know there’s someone else here. Something is toying with me. Beyond the light shining from inside the houses and the figures I keep glimpsing, there was one thing that proved I’m not going insane. There were dead larvae. I didn’t see what happened to them, when the fog cleared from where they were, something already took the life out of them.

There’s something in the fog.
</div></div></div><div class="light-overlay"></div></div>

== Events ==
<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
<div style="display: flex; background-color: rgba(60, 60, 70, 0.4); padding: 6px 10px; color: #E0E0E0; border: 1px solid #8888AA; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 0.9rem; text-align: center; width: 500px; margin-bottom: 15px">M.E.G. ADVISES: Do not attempt to interact with anomalies directly. Retreat immediately if you witness significant environmental change.</div></div>
Level 301, while appearing static and almost monotonous at first, is highly unstable the longer one remains inside. The environment reacts subtly to the wanderer’s presence, generating phenomena that can range from mildly disorienting to potentially lethal. Many wanderers reported encountering differents phenomenas, meaning the level probably generates random events depending on the wanderer. Altough, there were common events that happen to the majority of wanderers, all of them reported to date are:
