<p>
The files contained within the <span class="highlight">C.R.T.</span> are not directly accessible. 
Instead, each entry is locked behind a <span class="highlight">Gate</span> — a cryptographic marker 
embedded across multiple layers of the archive. Personel may encounter fragments of these Keys in 
the form of <span class="highlight">hidden codes, encrypted sequences, or patterns</span> 
scattered throughout the network. 
</p>
<p>
To retrieve a document, one must <span class="highlight">assemble the proper Key</span> and match 
it to the corresponding entry listed above. Only then can the requested file be accessed.  
</p>
<p>
