The only officially confirmed entities in this level are the faintly glowing larvaes, drifting silently along streets, alleys, and inside houses.
Many wanderers report feeling watched, waking from their comas in tears, begging researchers to acknowledge the presence of another entity. Officially, the M.E.G. dismisses these claims as hallucinations.

=== Glowing Larvae ===
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Blurimage|file=G_Larvae_191.png|hovertext=-- . -- --- .-. .. . ...|caption='''Glowing Larvae''', agrouped on a sidewalk.}}
The Glowing Larvae are luminescent organisms found throughout the level, roughly the size of a human hand. Their faint, pulsating glow is one of the few sources of light in the environment, becoming brighter when gathered in large groups. When isolated, their light gradually fades until it vanishes.

<span class="wds-button mw-customtoggle-sidebar3"><</span>
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-sidebar3">
<div class="sidebar-container">
<div class="sidebar-content">
<div class="story-box">
I haven’t slept since the last time I wrote. I don’t even know how much time has passed. Hours? Days? The fog doesn’t move. The wind keeps howling through the streets, but the mist just hangs there, heavy and still. The larvae are fewer now, dimmer, scattered like dying stars on the pavement. I tried following one of their trails deeper into the blocks, thinking it would lead me somewhere safe, but it only led me to more dead ends. More houses. More memories that aren’t mine.

I swear I heard your voice again. Not like before, not in the windows. This time it was closer, behind me, whispering my name over and over until it sounded wrong, distorted, like a recording played backward. When I turned around, nothing. Just fog.

I started taking more pictures with the camera. Each flash feel like I'm tearing open this place looking for something. I catch glimpses of… something tall, standing where the fog is thickest. Always at the edge of the light, always still. I remember it. But I know it’s moving when I’m not looking.

<div style="margin: -50px">[[File:237_Angel?.png|center|1920x1500]]</div>

If anyone finds this, I want you to tell my brother I love him and I'm s
</div></div></div><div class="light-overlay"></div></div>

They usually crawl in clusters, rarely seen alone, preferring wall corners and street curbs. Although they are entirely passive, some wanderers report being “guided” by them toward specific locations. The M.E.G., however, officially records such behavior as mere coincidence.

Wanderers may collect them in containers, but outside their clusters they quickly lose luminosity. When crushed, they release a strong odor that induces a vivid déjà vu of forgotten memories ranging from childhood recollections to experiences as far back as the womb. There are unconfirmed reports that ingesting one of these larvae results in a fatal mental overload, with individuals either seizuring or falling into deep comas.

The M.E.G. classifies the Glowing Larvae as “insignificant,” posing no direct threat. Any other hypotheses raised by wanderers are officially treated as hallucinations.

