== Entrances & Exits ==
=== Entrances ===
Current investigations indicate two ways of entering Level 301:
<div class="info-box">
=== Resurfacing Memory ===
Wanderers suffering from amnesia, dementia, Alzheimer’s, or even memory suppression caused by trauma have been reported to suddenly collapse when standing at the threshold of recalling what was forgotten. Their physical bodies remain in a comatose state in baseline reality, while their consciousness transitions into this Level.
</div>
<br>
<div class="info-box">
=== Void Parasites ===
Until then, the M.E.G. had an unknown threat killing their agents and wanderers with a very slim chance to happen during a noclip. They displayed a grotesque anomaly; insectoid organisms attached to the back of their heads, partially embedded beneath the scalp. These parasites resemble a hybrid between centipedes and beetles, covered in a viscous black secretion. Anchored by multiple claw-like appendages, the creature inserts a long, needle-like proboscis deep into the skull, extending all the way to the hippocampus. At the tip, the proboscis appears to partially dissolve and bind itself directly to neural tissue, releasing unknown compounds into the brain<ref>Among these compounds, at least one has been identified by independent researchers as Liquid Pain.</ref>.It was later discovered by an agent wich miraculously "woke up from the dead" that, while falling through the void, something attached to his head and somehow took him to '''Level 301'''.
<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
<div style="display: flex; background-color: rgba(60, 60, 70, 0.4); padding: 6px 10px; color: #E0E0E0; border: 1px solid #8888AA; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 0.9rem; text-align: center; width: 500px; margin-bottom: 15px">M.E.G. documentation has chosen not to release further details, officially categorizing these organisms as “postmortem anomalies” rather than active threats.</div></div>
</div>

=== Exits ===
There are three commonly reported (though not officially confirmed) ways of exiting the Level:
<div class="info-box">
=== The Crimson Sun ===
A few reports mention the distant appearance of a massive red sun rising at the horizon. Allegedly, approaching it leads to an exit, though no M.E.G. expedition has been able to replicate this phenomenon.
</div>
